%F A299900 From _Steven Kotlarz_, Jun 25 2026: (Start)
%F A299900 Conjectured g.f., empirically corroborated by the 501-term table below: A(x) = P(x)/Q(x), where P and Q are given in the linked PARI and Python programs as coefficient lists in ascending powers of x.
%F A299900 Q(x) = (1-x)^3 * Phi(3,x)^2 * Phi(4,x)^2 * Phi(6,x) * Phi(7,x) * Phi(8,x) * Phi(9,x) * Phi(12,x) * Phi(16,x) * Phi(21,x).
%F A299900 Equivalently, the low-to-high coefficients of Q(x) are [1, -2, 3, -3, 3, -3, 4, -5, 6, -7, 8, -9, 9, -9, 9, -10, 10, -10, 9, -9, 9, -10, 10, -10, 9, -8, 7, -7, 8, -9, 10, -10, 10, -9, 9, -9, 10, -10, 10, -9, 9, -9, 9, -8, 7, -6, 5, -4, 3, -3, 3, -3, 2, -1].
%F A299900 The corresponding degree-53 recurrence from Q is satisfied by the 501-term table for n = 58..500. For this conjectured g.f. the quasi-polynomial form is a(n) = (11/7)*n^2 + b(n mod 12)*n + c(n mod 1008), for n >= 5, where b = [-58/63, -389/504, -52/63, -443/504, -46/63, -437/504, -58/63, -347/504, -52/63, -485/504, -46/63, -395/504]. The constant coefficient c has period 1008.
%F A299900 The denominator above is the reduced degree-53 denominator. The earlier OEIS gfun recurrence has order 58 because its denominator is x^5*Q(x), i.e., the five leading zero shift coefficients have been retained. (End)
